Interface Command

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CommandTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CommandStub

    public interface Command
extends Service, CommandTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The Command interface provides methods to get information about command line interface (CLI) commands.

      • list

        Command.ListInvocation list()
        Returns the identifiers of all commands, or commands in a specific namespace.

        Invocation Result:
        Identifiers of the requested commands.

        Returns:
        instance of Command.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if a namespace corresponding to path doesn't exist.

      • get

        Command.GetInvocation get(CommandTypes.Identity identity)
        Retrieves information about a command including information about how to execute that command.

        Invocation Result:
        Information about the command including information about how to execute that command.

        Parameters:
        identity - Identifier of the command for which to retreive information.
        Returns:
        instance of Command.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if a command corresponding to identity doesn't exist.

      • fingerprint

        Command.FingerprintInvocation fingerprint()
        Returns the aggregate fingerprint of all the command metadata from all the metadata sources.

        The fingerprint provides clients an efficient way to check if the metadata for commands has been modified on the server.

        Invocation Result:
        Fingerprint of all the command metadata present on the server.

        Returns:
        instance of Command.FingerprintInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described fingerprint operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
